    <svcsubsec id="x08290120">
        <title>AIR HORNS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f08290912">air horn function diagram</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f08290912" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08290912.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Air Horn Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. AIR SOLENOID PACK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. AIR HORN FOOT SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. AIR HORN</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The air horn provides the driver audio warning to warn others.</para>
            <para>The air horn switch is a direct power source to the air horn solenoid. When the horn button is pushed
                power is applied to the air horn solenoid.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
